article.headline: Howard 75, Winston-Salem 63
article.story: WASHINGTON -- C.J. Prince scored a career-high 21 points and hit three 3-pointers during a key stretch Saturday as Howard defeated Winston-Salem State 75-63 for its first win since opening night. Randy Hampton and Kyle Riley added 14 points apiece for the Bison (2-14), who had lost 14 straight after defeating Oregon State at home on Nov. 14. Jamal Durham and Brian Fisher each scored 15 points for the Rams (4-11), who suffered their third straight loss while comitting 20 turnovers. Prince, in his third game with the Bison after transferring from Maryland-Eastern Shore, hit three 3-pointers to key a 21-10 second-half run. He made the last one from the right wing for a 66-51 Howard lead. The Rams cut the gap to 66-57 on McIntoche Alcius's free throw, but never pulled closer. Eugene Myatt became the 18th Bison to eclipse 1,000 career points. He has 1,009.
